Entry.64:
Changed all our gear into another tent. Told to be ready to-night for operations. At five o’clock we got our orders to pack up a few instruments and (
and
 ) operating table to go to a place called Eblingheim to do operating work. The excitement of the previous days had given me a splitting headache, a thing that is becoming a regularity. The officers getting to hear of this prevented me from going and with this I was more than pleased
